I am not sure if we need "UpgradeImpact" flag for this fix as we are taking care of backward compatibility. If no unit is specified (as is the older case) we are assuming Bytes - this behavior is consistent with what's currently happening.

I agree this is not really a bug fix but a minor enhancement.
But I see no negative impact of this as we are taking care
of backward and compatibility and ignoring any wrong input and
falling back to default -- that is no limit.
